## <a id="overview"></a>Overview

This guide describes Pivotal Telemetry Collector, a stand-alone tool, and light-weight alternative
to the Pivotal Telemetry for Ops Manager tile. It can be used manually as a CLI or automated through
Concourse. The tool can be configured and automated to share product usage and consumption data with Pivotal
so that we can improve our products and services based on insights from real-world usage.

## <a id="getting-an-api-key"></a>Getting an API Key

Get your Telemetry API key from the Pivotal contacts that you work with, or by emailing the Pivotal Telemetry team at pivotal-telemetry-support@pivotal.io.

## <a id="getting-started"></a>Getting Started

1. Download the [Pivotal Telemetry Collector from Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/products/pivotal-telemetry-collector/).
1. Agree to the End User License Agreement (EULA) that’s presented at the time of download. This indicates your intent to participate in the Pivotal Telemetry Program.
1. Get your Telemetry API key from the Pivotal contacts that you work with, or by emailing the Pivotal Telemetry team at pivotal-telemetry-support@pivotal.io.
1. Run and configure the Pivotal Telemetry Collector CLI. For guidance, see the Configuration Reference section.

## <a id="requirements"></a>Requirements

To use Pivotal Telemetry Collector, you will need the following:

  - A currently supported version of Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF)
    Ops Manager
  - Pivotal Telemetry Collector API credentials provided by Pivotal
  - The ability to enable egress from the Telemetry Collector to `https://telemetry.pivotal.io` on port `443`.


## <a id="access-to-data"></a>Access to Data

Data collected from your environments will be made available to the Pivotal teams that you work with and presented to you through PDF reports. We are iteratively building new ways for you to access your data in the future.

